<div type="commentary">
<head>Commentary</head>
<p>One of the series of dedications from the East Court of the Hadrianic Baths: <xref type="iAph">1184</xref>, <xref type="iAph">1186</xref>, <xref type="iAph">1187</xref>, <xref type="iAph">1188</xref>, <xref type="iAph">1189</xref>, <xref type="iAph">1190</xref>, <xref type="iAph">1191</xref>, <xref type="iAph">1192</xref>, <xref type="iAph">1193</xref>, <xref type="iAph">1195</xref>, <xref type="iAph">1196</xref>, <xref type="iAph">1197</xref>, <xref type="iAph">1198</xref>, <xref type="iAph">1199</xref>, <xref type="iAph">1200</xref>, <xref type="iAph">1201</xref>, <xref type="iAph">1202</xref>, <xref type="iAph">1203</xref>, <xref type="iAph">1204</xref>, <xref type="iAph">1205</xref>, <xref type="iAph">1206</xref>, <xref type="iAph">1207</xref>, <xref type="iAph">1208</xref>, <xref type="iAph">1209</xref>, <xref type="iAph">1210</xref> ; all are by women, and apparently bore caryatids (see <xref type="iAph">1198</xref>).</p><p>The editor of Boulanger Book C assumed that this should be taken with <xref type="iAph">xx</xref> (=Museum 4); but the description of the egg &amp; dart moulding rules this out. Another hand suggests ref. to <xref type="iAph">1191</xref> (=no. 4 above); but it can't quite fit.</p>
</div>
